STANLIB Multi-Strategy Stochastic Modelling

Frontier Report: TEST

We use an adjusted emperical copula to generate 100 simulated 260-week portfolio return paths. An emperical copula is selected to maintain higher-moments and historical returns are scaled to for forward estimates of prospective returns and volatility. Historical sample size was 1040-weeks; multi-factor regression models may be applied to extend timeseries of assets with short histories.
